# Slooze Take-Home Assignment (Backend)

This repository contains the backend implementation for the Slooze take-home challenge.
The project focuses on authentication, role-based access control, and business logic
for a food ordering system.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- Prisma ORM
- SQLite
- JWT Authentication

## Roles
- ADMIN
- MANAGER
- MEMBER

## Features
- JWT-based authentication
- Role-based access control (RBAC) enforced at API level
- Country-based restaurant filtering (India / America)
- Restaurants and menu items
- Order creation
- Checkout and cancellation restricted to Admin and Manager

## API Endpoints

### Auth
- POST `/auth/login`

### Restaurants
- GET `/restaurants` (protected)

### Orders
- POST `/orders`
- POST `/orders/checkout` (Admin, Manager only)
- POST `/orders/cancel` (Admin, Manager only)

## Running the Project Locally

```bash
npm install
npx prisma migrate reset
node server.js
